## Verified API Capabilities

Confirmed via real API calls:

| Endpoint | What it does | Custom attributes? |
|---|---|---|
| `GET /organizations/{org}/trace/{traceId}/?additional_attributes=X&additional_attributes=Y` | Trace tree with named extra attrs | **Yes** — must enumerate attribute names as query params |
| `GET /projects/{org}/{project}/trace-items/{itemId}/?trace_id={traceId}&item_type=spans` | Single span full detail | **Yes** — returns ALL attributes automatically, no enumeration needed |
| `GET /organizations/{org}/events/?dataset=spans&field=X&field=Y` | Span list/search | **Yes** — must enumerate field names |
| `GET /organizations/{org}/trace-items/attributes/?itemType=spans` | Discover available attribute keys | N/A — returns attribute names for column picker |

Key insight: The trace detail endpoint already supports `additional_attributes` — we just weren't passing the query parameter.

