## Workstream 1: Skill/Docs + `--since` Alias (Items 1-3)

### Problem
AI agents repeatedly try non-existent flags: `--since` (should be `--period`), `--project` (should be positional), `--trace` on `span list` (should be positional).

### 1A: Add `--since` as alias for `--period`

The most natural flag name for time filtering. Add it as an alias on all commands that have `--period`.

**Files to modify:**
- `src/commands/trace/list.ts` — add `since: "period"` to aliases
- `src/commands/span/list.ts` — add `since: "period"` to aliases
- Any other commands with a `period` flag (check `LIST_PERIOD_FLAG` usage)

### 1B: Reinforce correct patterns in agent guidance

**File:** `docs/src/content/docs/agent-guidance.md` — add positive examples to "Common Mistakes" section, framed as "how to do it right":

```markdown
### Time filtering
Use `--period` (alias `-t` or `--since`) to filter by time window:
  sentry trace list --period 1h
  sentry span list --since 24h
  sentry span list -t 7d

### Scoping to an org or project
Org and project are positional arguments following `gh` CLI conventions:
  sentry trace list my-org/my-project
  sentry issue list my-org/my-project
  sentry span list my-org/my-project/abc123def456...

### Listing spans in a trace
Pass the trace ID as a positional argument:
  sentry span list abc123def456...
  sentry span list my-org/my-project/abc123def456...
```

