## Workstream 4: Filter Zero-Valued Measurements (Item 6 Mitigation)

### Problem
Every span in `trace view --json` includes zero-valued web vitals measurements. Confirmed these come from the Sentry API — the trace detail endpoint always includes the hardcoded measurement columns. Non-browser spans have all zeros.

### Solution
Filter out all-zero measurements in the JSON output. Non-zero measurements (like on the root `pageload` span) are preserved.

### Files to modify

**`src/commands/trace/view.ts`** and **`src/commands/span/view.ts`** — In the JSON transform, filter measurements:

```typescript
// When including measurements in output:
if (span.measurements) {
  const nonZero = Object.fromEntries(
    Object.entries(span.measurements).filter(([, v]) => v !== 0)
  );
  if (Object.keys(nonZero).length > 0) {
    result.measurements = nonZero;
  }
}
```

This reduces JSON size by ~40% for typical traces and eliminates the "bogus web vitals" noise.

### Verification
- `bun test test/commands/trace/view.func.test.ts test/commands/span/view.func.test.ts`

